\date{2026-04-15T00:55:24Z}
\title{Function}
\taxon{Definition}

\p{Given two sets #{A} and #{B}, a function from #{A} to #{B} is a mapping that takes each element #{x\in A} to a single element of #{B}. ##{f:A\rightarrow B}}
\p{#{f(x)} represents the element of #{B} associated with #{x} by #{f}.##{B=\{y\in B: y=f(x) \text{ for some } x\in A\}}}
\p{The domain of #{f} is the set #{A}. The range of #{f} is some subset of #{B}, not necessarily equal to #{B}.}